The results of statistical modelling are illustrated in Table 2
. Two variables, ‘number of animals/herd’ and ‘year of sampling’, acted as risk factors for the seroprevalence of PPV. The odds ratio (OR) for seropositivity to PPV increased 12-fold for each additional 50 animals/herd. Increasing ORs for the presence of PPV antibodies were detected from samples collected earlier in the study period. The highest OR (3.9) for PCV2 antibodies was found in 2007, while the years 2006 and 2008 had similar ratios (1.8). Farms in Eastern Finland had lower ORs (0.2) in relation to seroprevalence to PCV2 (Table 3
).
